      "content": "It makes sense that you feel a deep void when the part of you that once felt alive seems to have vanished. This feeling that there is no future \"you\" waiting to return is a heavy but real experience, even though it doesn't necessarily mean you've lost your capacity to feel again. While the journey to reclaim your identity can feel endless, connecting with a professional who understands this specific sense of emptiness can offer tools to help you find meaning beyond just \"staying in the room.\" Please remember that support is available if you need to carry through these difficult thoughts right now.",
